-- Uganda Raises Oil Reserves to 3.5 Billion Barrels on New Finds
-- B y   F r e d   O j a m b o
-- 2012-09-17T10:21:33Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-17/uganda-raises-oil-reserves-to-3-5-billion-barrels-on-new-finds.html
Uganda  raised its oil reserves by
40 percent to 3.5 billion barrels after two further discoveries
last year, Commissioner for Petroleum Ernest Rubondo said.  The increase comes after the completion of appraisals of
the two fields as well as 10 existing exploration fields,
Rubondo said today by phone from Entebbe, near  Kampala , the
capital.  The two discoveries are in exploration area 1 and the
existing 10 fields are in exploration areas 1 and 2  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Ojambo in Kampala at 
 fojambo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
